, creation timestamp\n- Tasks start in \"pending\" state, transition to \"processing\"\n- Returns null if no tasks available\n- Track pending task count\n\n**Phase 2: Named Queues** (`/workspace/phases/phase-02.md`)\n- Multiple independent queues with names\n- Default queue if no name specified\n- List all queue names\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n- Per-queue isolation\n\n**Phase 3: Priority** (`/workspace/phases/phase-03.md`)\n- Priority levels 1-10 (1=highest, default=5)\n- Higher priority (lower number) returned first\n- Same priority: FIFO order\n- Priority per queue\n- Invalid priorities raise errors\n\n**Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks** (`/workspace/phases/phase-04.md`)\n- Tasks can have delay (ms) or specific availability time\n- Delayed tasks don't return until available\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple delayed tasks ordered by: availability time → priority → FIFO\n- Works with named queues\n\n**Phase 5: Retry with Backoff** (`/workspace/phases/phase-05.md`)\n- Mark tasks as completed or failed\n- Auto-retry on failure with exponential backoff: baseDelay * 2^(attempt-1)\n- Configurable max retries (default 3) and base delay (default 1000ms)\n- Track attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep queue and priority\n- Failed tasks after retries exhausted remain in failed state\n\n**Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue** (`/workspace/phases/phase-06.md`)\n- Tasks with exhausted retries move to DLQ\n- View all dead-lettered tasks\n- DLQ retains error info and failure count\n- Requeue dead-lettered tasks for fresh retries\n- Clear DLQ\n- Per-queue DLQs\n\n**Phase 7: Task Dependencies** (`/workspace/phases/phase-07.md`)\n- Tasks can depend on other task IDs\n- Blocked tasks until dependencies complete\n- Check dependencies unblocked when depended task completes\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at creation\n- Error on non-existent task dependencies\n- Failed dependency doesn't fail dependents\n- Inspect task dependency status\n\n**Phase 8: Concurrency Control** (`/workspace/phases/phase-08.md`)\n- Per-queue max concurrency limit\n- Returns null if limit reached despite pending tasks\n- Completing/failing a task frees a slot\n- Default: unlimited concurrency\n- Query concurrency limit and active count\n- Respects priority ordering within concurrency constraints\n\n**Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation** (`/workspace/phases/phase-09.md`)\n- Processing tasks report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates with notifications\n- Unsubscribe capability\n- Cancel pending/processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n**Phase 10: Recurring Tasks** (`/workspace/phases/phase-10.md`)\n- Schedules with cron expressions and task template\n- Supported cron: `*/N * * * *` (every N minutes), `0 * * * *` (hourly), `0 0 * * *` (daily)\n- Create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism for testing\n- Recurring tasks subject to all queue rules\n- Stop occurrences when schedule removed\n\n**Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline** (`/workspace/phases/phase-11.md`)\n- Per-queue middleware registration\n- Middleware intercepts tasks before handler\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Can skip processing by not calling \"next\"\n- Can modify tasks\n- Error in middleware marks task as failed\n- Processing function/handler per queue\n- Independent middleware stacks per queue\n\n**Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown** (`/workspace/phases/phase-12.md`)\n- Stop accepting new tasks on shutdown\n- Adding tasks raises error after shutdown\n- Wait for processing tasks with configurable timeout\n- Force-cancel tasks exceeding timeout\n- Register shutdown callbacks\n- Provide summary: completed, force-cancelled, duration\n- Safe to call multiple times\n- Immediate completion if no tasks processing\n\n### Source Code\n\n**src/** (`/workspace/src/`)\n- Currently empty except for `.gitkeep`\n- Sh