+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M2NQB91fn5Vtvmt8q13ptX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n     2→\n     3→Add the ability to defer tasks so they only become available for processing after a specified time.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- A task can be given a delay (in milliseconds) or a specific future time at which it becomes available.\n     8→- Delayed tasks are added to the queue immediately but are not returned when retrieving until their availability time has passed.\n     9→- Non-delayed tasks are always preferred over delayed tasks that are not yet available.\n    10→- When multiple delayed tasks become available simultaneously, they should be ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO.\n    11→- The task object should indicate when it becomes available.\n    12→- Delays work correctly with named queues.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77b6fef8-4f38-4e2c-be4a-9efaa031aac7","uuid":"d506243c-a69a-40ec-bc52-5d7a4322f7ac","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/phases/phase-04.md","content":"# Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n\nAdd the ability to defer tasks so they only become available for processing after a specified time.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- A task can be given a delay (in milliseconds) or a specific future time at which it becomes available.\n- Delayed tasks are added to the queue immediately but are not returned when retrieving until their availability time has passed.\n- Non-delayed tasks are always preferred over delayed tasks that are not yet available.\n- When multiple delayed tasks become available simultaneously, they should be ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO.\n- The task object should indicate when it becomes available.\n- Delays work correctly with named queues.\n","numLines":13,"startLine":1,"totalLines":13}}}
